result.execSummary:
The defendant Rachael L Howen-Franks was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Aggravated Battery [Modifiers: Repeater], a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 940.19(6).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Sentencing hearing on December 1, 2016 at 11:00 am.

Defendant Rachael L Howen-Franks in court with attorney Eric Sheets. Defendant Rachael L Howen-Franks in custody. Elizabeth R. Constable appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Cases heard today are 16CF33 and 15CM498.

11:13 a.m.   Court calls case and states the appearances.

Plea questionnaire/Agreement filed.
Prosecutor states plea agreement.
Attorney for Defendant concurs with agreement stated.
Atty Sheets is not requesting a PSI but the State is.
Atty Constable makes her statement regarding her request for the PSI and that it is necessary and states her reasons on the record.
Atty Sheets is ready to proceed with a plea but would then request a short form PSI as they were ready to proceed to sentencing today also.

Defendant enters a plea of: 
16CF33:
Count 1 - No contest 
Count 2 - DRI
Count 3 - DRI

15CM498:
Count 1 - No contest 
Count 2 - DRI

Court questions Defendant regarding plea.
Court informs Defendant of Constitutional Rights. Court advises Defendant of Elements State must prove for the Charge.
Court questions Attorney for Defendant.
Court finds Defendant's Plea is freely, voluntarily and intelligently made.
Attorneys stipulate that there is factual basis for the charge(s).

BY THE COURT:
Court finds a sufficient factual basis to support the charge(s).
Court finds the defendant guilty on Count 1 of 16CF33 and Count 1 of 15CM498 and Counts 2 & 3 on 16CF33 are DRI and Count 1 on 15CM498 is DRI.  Clerk directed to enter Judgment of Conviction this date.
Court questions Atty Sheets if his client has had a PSI on any other case; she has had one approx. in 2004.

BY THE COURT:
PSI ordered and will need to be provided no later than 11/23/16 and provided to all parties  Sentencing hearing scheduled for December 1, 2016 at 11:00 am.

Court addresses Case 12FO988 with a warrant for non-payment of fines.
Atty Constable would request that the the warrant be quashed and a civil judgment be entered.
This is stipulated by both parties.

BY THE COURT:
Warrant is quashed and civil judgment to be entered for the amount of $50.95 and $210.60.
